---
/**
 * ai-security/0001 · Figure 1 — the hero, "The prompt is not a trust boundary".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/ai-security/lessons/0001-ai-threat-model-and-prompt-injection.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size,
 * stroke-width, marker-end, font-style, …). In an .astro file the SVG is plain
 * HTML, so it renders byte-for-byte.
 *
 * The source page defined four shared arrowhead markers (arw, arwG, arwR, arwM)
 * once in a hidden <svg> at the top of <body>. Since each figure is now a
 * standalone component, those marker <defs> are embedded inline here (and in
 * every figure that references them) so the figure renders correctly on its own,
 * independent of render order. Marker ids are kept as-is to match the source DOM.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 320"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The agent stack with its trust boundaries: untrusted user input and retrieved content flow into the model, which can act through tools; the real controls sit on the retrieval query and the tool layer, not on the prompt."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwM"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#b5179e"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="20" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >The prompt is not a trust boundary</text
        >

        <!-- untrusted sources -->
        <rect
            x="28"
            y="44"
            width="150"
            height="40"
            rx="8"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="103" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >User input</text
        >
        <text x="103" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >direct injection</text
        >
        <rect
            x="28"
            y="96"
            width="150"
            height="40"
            rx="8"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="103" y="114" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >Retrieved docs / web</text
        >
        <text x="103" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >indirect injection</text
        >
        <text x="103" y="156" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#9a2417"
            >all attacker-reachable</text
        >

        <!-- boundary 1: retrieval query -->
        <line
            x1="178"
            y1="116"
            x2="244"
            y2="116"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <rect
            x="200"
            y="168"
            width="120"
            height="34"
            rx="6"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="260" y="184" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Boundary 1</text
        >
        <text x="260" y="196" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >retrieval query · ACL</text
        >

        <!-- the model / context window -->
        <rect
            x="244"
            y="62"
            width="150"
            height="74"
            rx="10"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="319" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >LLM + context window</text
        >
        <text x="319" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >ONE channel: data and</text
        >
        <text x="319" y="115" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >instructions look identical</text
        >
        <text x="319" y="129" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#9a2417"
            >can't enforce a boundary</text
        >
        <line
            x1="178"
            y1="64"
            x2="242"
            y2="78"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.3"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>

        <!-- boundary 2: tool layer -->
        <line
            x1="394"
            y1="99"
            x2="460"
            y2="99"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <rect
            x="412"
            y="168"
            width="120"
            height="34"
            rx="6"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="472" y="184" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Boundary 2</text
        >
        <text x="472" y="196" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >tools · least priv + egress</text
        >

        <!-- tools / actions -->
        <rect
            x="460"
            y="62"
            width="150"
            height="40"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef2f7"
            stroke="#1f3a5a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="535" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Tools take actions</text
        >
        <text x="535" y="94" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >email · DB · fetch URL</text
        >
        <rect
            x="460"
            y="112"
            width="150"
            height="36"
            rx="8"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.2"></rect>
        <text x="535" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >outbound = exfil path</text
        >
        <text x="535" y="141" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >if egress is open</text
        >

        <!-- dotted boundary links -->
        <line
            x1="260"
            y1="168"
            x2="290"
            y2="138"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <line
            x1="472"
            y1="168"
            x2="500"
            y2="104"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>

        <text x="320" y="236" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-style="italic" fill="#b5179e"
            >The model is in the blast radius, not on the perimeter. You can't secure it from inside
            the prompt.</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="262" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >Two real boundaries: scope what gets retrieved (ACL in the query) and what tools can do
            (least privilege + egress).</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="290" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >OWASP LLM01 prompt injection · root cause: data and instructions share one channel.</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="310" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >No layer is complete. The posture is layered controls + least privilege +
            assume-breach.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The hero of the whole track. Untrusted text enters from the user <em>and</em> from anything retrieved;
        the model can't tell it from your instructions; the only enforceable boundaries are the <b
            >retrieval query</b
        > (who can see what) and the <b>tool layer</b> (what the agent can do and where it can send).<sup
            ><a href="#s1" id="r1b">1</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
